      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blind bake the shell",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make a shortcrust from 200 g {{plain-flour}}, 100 g cold {{unsalted-butter}}, {{fine-salt}}, and 2-3 tbsp cold water. Chill 30 minutes, roll out, and line a 23 cm pie dish. Chill 20 more minutes. Heat the oven to 200°C (180°C fan). Blind bake with baking paper and beans for 15 minutes, remove beans and paper, bake 8-10 minutes more until fully golden and dry. Cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook the custard",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk together the {{caster-sugar}}, {{cornflour}}, and {{cocoa-powder}} in a medium saucepan. Whisk in the {{whole-milk}} gradually until smooth. Set over medium heat and cook, stirring constantly with a whisk, until the mixture thickens and begins to boil (about 8-10 minutes). Reduce the heat to low and cook for 2 more minutes, still stirring: this cooks out the starch taste. Remove from the heat. Whisk the {{egg-yolks}} in a bowl, then whisk in a ladleful of the hot custard to temper them. Pour the egg mixture back into the pan and return to low heat, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the {{dark-chocolate}}, {{unsalted-butter}}, and {{vanilla-extract}} until smooth.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and chill",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the hot custard into the cooled shell. Press cling film directly against the surface to prevent a skin. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours until fully set. Top with whipped {{double-cream}} before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
